The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning systems (DL) based on Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) in various aspects of our life, including unmanned vehicles, speech processing, and robotics. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on testing DL systems, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
